-- HSBC Global Asset Management appoints new global bond team chief
-- 
-- Fri May 09, 2014 11:05AM EDT
-- None



LONDON, May 9 (Reuters) - HSBC Global Asset Management <HSBA.L> said on Friday it had appointed Ernst Osiander as head of its global bond team in London.

He replaces Guy Dunham, who handed over his fund responsibilities in January and has since left the firm, it said in a statement. Osiander's team manages the group's global and sterling fixed income portfolios.